\displaystyle \int \left( \frac{1}{x^2+3} \right)\; dx
u=x^2+3
u=\frac{x}{\sqrt{3}}
x = \sqrt{3} \tan\theta
dx = \sqrt{3}\cdot\sec^{2}\theta \ d\theta
u = \frac{x}{\sqrt{3}}
du = \frac 1{\sqrt{3}} dx
 \int \left( \frac 1{x^2+3} \right) dx = \int \left( \frac 1{(\sqrt 3 u)^2 + 3} \, \sqrt 3 \right) dx = \frac 1{\sqrt{3}} \int \left( \frac 1{u^2 + 1} \right) = \frac 1{\sqrt{3}} \arctan(u) + C. 
